# sdk-hooks.mk.example
#
# Reference example for the provider-owned SDK codegen hooks contract exposed by
# the ci-mgmt-generated Makefile. This file is NOT consumed by anything: copy it
# into your provider repo root as `sdk-hooks.mk`, then keep only the slots you
# need. ci-mgmt never creates `sdk-hooks.mk` for you, and regenerating CI does
# not overwrite it, so it is a regen-safe escape hatch for fine-tuning
# `pulumi package gen-sdk` (and legacy codegen) output.
#
# Contract
# --------
# The generated Makefile `-include`s `sdk-hooks.mk` (the leading `-` means "no
# error if absent") and invokes two slots around each per-language SDK codegen
# recipe, in BOTH the gen-sdk and the legacy codegen branches:
#
#   PRE_GEN_SDK_<LANG>    runs immediately before the codegen step
#   POST_GEN_SDK_<LANG>   runs immediately after codegen, before the recipe's
#                         completion sentinel is touched
#
# <LANG> is the uppercased SDK language. The full set of slots is:
#
#   PRE_GEN_SDK_GO       POST_GEN_SDK_GO
#   PRE_GEN_SDK_NODEJS   POST_GEN_SDK_NODEJS
#   PRE_GEN_SDK_PYTHON   POST_GEN_SDK_PYTHON
#   PRE_GEN_SDK_DOTNET   POST_GEN_SDK_DOTNET
#   PRE_GEN_SDK_JAVA     POST_GEN_SDK_JAVA
#
# Each slot is a plain make variable expanded as a recipe line. An undefined or
# empty slot expands to nothing and make skips it entirely, so leaving a slot
# unset is a true no-op. A slot value is a shell command line; it runs from the
# provider repo root (the same working directory as the codegen recipe). For
# anything non-trivial, point the slot at a checked-in script so the Makefile
# stays readable and the logic is testable on its own:
#
#   POST_GEN_SDK_GO = ./scripts/fixup-go-sdk.sh
#
# Multiple commands are supported via a recipe-style continuation or by calling
# out to a script. Prefer a script.
#
# Worked example
# --------------
# pulumi-pulumiservice needs to drop a generated file from the Go SDK and patch
# a Python type stub after each regeneration. With `sdk-hooks.mk` in the repo
# root containing:
#
#   POST_GEN_SDK_GO     = rm -f sdk/go/pulumiservice/internal/unused.go
#   POST_GEN_SDK_PYTHON = ./scripts/patch-python-stubs.sh
#
# running `make generate_go` deletes the stray file right after gen-sdk emits
# it, and `make generate_python` runs the stub patcher. No other language is
# affected, and removing `sdk-hooks.mk` restores stock behavior.

# --- copy the slots you need below and delete the rest ---

# PRE_GEN_SDK_GO     =
# POST_GEN_SDK_GO    =

# PRE_GEN_SDK_NODEJS  =
# POST_GEN_SDK_NODEJS =

# PRE_GEN_SDK_PYTHON  =
# POST_GEN_SDK_PYTHON =

# PRE_GEN_SDK_DOTNET  =
# POST_GEN_SDK_DOTNET =

# PRE_GEN_SDK_JAVA    =
# POST_GEN_SDK_JAVA   =
